"# Appendix B — Introspection cheat-sheet: one page per verb

Print this page. Keep it next to your keyboard.

Every introspection verb the book covered, in one place, with one-line usage.

## B.1 Verb metadata

**help name → record.** Get the full metadata record for a verb.
```
(help 'map)
```

**describe name → string.** Get a human-readable paragraph.
```
(describe 'map)
```

**doc-of name → string.** Get just the doc string.
```
(doc-of 'map)
```

**contract-of name → string.** Get the contract signature.
```
(contract-of 'map)
```

**arity-of name → int-or-list.** Get the arity.
```
(arity-of 'map)
```

**source-of name → path:line.** Get the source pointer.
```
(source-of 'map)
```

**examples-of name → list.** Get the tiered examples.
```
(examples-of 'map)
```

## B.2 Value shape

**type-of value → symbol.** Get the runtime type.
```
(type-of 42)
```

**length value → integer.** Get length of list or string.
```
(length '(1 2 3))
```

**keys hash → list.** Get keys of a hash.
```
(keys my-hash)
```

**values hash → list.** Get values of a hash.
```
(values my-hash)
```

**record-type record → symbol.** Get the type tag of a record.
```
(record-type alice)
```

**record-fields record → list.** Get the field names.
```
(record-fields alice)
```

**record-field record field → any.** Get a specific field.
```
(record-field alice :name)
```

## B.3 Predicates

Every runtime type has a predicate:
- `integer?` `real?` `number?`
- `string?` `symbol?` `char?`
- `boolean?`
- `list?` `pair?` `null?`
- `procedure?`
- `hash?` `vector?` `record?`
- `error?` `port?`

Usage:
```
(number? 42)   ;; #t
(string? 42)   ;; #f
```

## B.4 Environments

**current-env → env.** Get the current environment.
```
(current-env)
```

**env-vars env → list.** Enumerate bindings in a frame.
```
(env-vars (current-env))
```

**env-parent env → env-or-nil.** Get the parent env.
```
(env-parent (current-env))
```

**closure-env closure → env.** Get a closure's captured env (Wave 2).
```
(closure-env add5)
```

## B.5 Macros

**macroexpand form → form.** Fully expand a form.
```
(macroexpand '(when x y))
```

**macroexpand-1 form → form.** One step of expansion.
```
(macroexpand-1 '(unless x y))
```

**REPL:** `,expand <expr>` — same as macroexpand, prints result.

## B.6 Reader

**parse string → list-of-forms.** Reader.
```
(parse \"(+ 1 2)\")
```

**form-pos form → position.** Source position of a form.
```
(form-pos my-form)
```

## B.7 Errors

**last-error → error.** Most recent error.
```
(last-error)
```

**error-message error → string.** Message field.
```
(error-message e)
```

**error-kind error → symbol.** Kind tag.
```
(error-kind e)
```

**error-location error → position.** Where it happened.
```
(error-location e)
```

**error-stack error → list.** Call stack.
```
(error-stack e)
```

**error-cause error → error-or-nil.** Wrapped underlying error.
```
(error-cause e)
```

**error-context error → alist.** Structured context.
```
(error-context e)
```

## B.8 Trace and watch

**REPL:** `,trace <verb>` — start tracing a verb.
**REPL:** `,untrace <verb>` — stop tracing.
**REPL:** `,trace-log <verb>` — show the log.
**REPL:** `,watch <expr>` — add expression to watch list.

Programmatic:
```
(trace-log 'my-verb)
```

## B.9 Cortex

**cortex/read key → value.** Simple KV read.
```
(cortex/read 'my-key)
```

**cortex/write key value → boolean.** Simple KV write.
```
(cortex/write 'my-key 42)
```

**cortex/record :subject :predicate :object :at :source → boolean.** Structured write.
```
(cortex/record :subject 'user :predicate 'preferred-color :object 'red :at (current-second) :source 'ui-click)
```

**cortex/query :subject :predicate :object :at :source :order-by :limit → list.** Query.
```
(cortex/query :subject 'user :predicate 'preferred-color)
```

## B.10 Registry

**snapshot-registry → hash.** Full registry as data.
```
(snapshot-registry)
```

**hasVerb name → boolean.** Membership test.
```
(has-verb 'map)
```

## B.11 Search

**apropos regex → list.** Match by name.
```
(apropos \"sort\")
```

**verbs-in-namespace ns → list.** Match by namespace.
```
(verbs-in-namespace \"cortex\")
```

**REPL:** `,apropos <regex>` — same as apropos, prints.
**REPL:** `,namespace <ns>` — same as verbs-in-namespace.

## B.12 LLM-augmented

**llm/ask prompt → string.** Ask the model.
**llm/complete partial → string.** Complete an expression.
**llm/config → alist.** Describe the model binding.
**what-is symbol → record.** Grounded lookup.
**explain form → string.** Prose explanation.
**shape-of value → record.** Mechanical + interpretive.
**reason-about value → string.** Provenance prose.
**fix error → form.** Suggested fix.
**pretty-error error → string.** Human-readable rewrite.
**did-you-mean symbol → list.** Nearest verb names.

## B.13 Composer

**composer/canvas → canvas-record.** Container.
**composer/emit canvas → form.** Canvas to form.
**composer/apply canvas form → canvas.** Form to canvas.
**composer/save canvas path → path.** Persist to disk.
**composer/load path → canvas.** Read from disk.

Widget verbs: `composer/slider`, `composer/button`, `composer/piano-roll`, `composer/sprite-grid`, `composer/tile-map`, `composer/timeline`, `composer/adsr`, `composer/instrument-picker`, `composer/fx-chain`, `composer/text-field`, `composer/toggle`, `composer/color-picker`, `composer/live-code`.

## B.14 Performance

**current-time-ms → number.** Wall clock milliseconds.
**current-fuel → integer.** Remaining fuel budget.
**allocated-bytes → integer.** Bytes allocated so far.
**gc-info → alist.** GC stats.

**REPL:** `,time <expr>` — measure wall time.

## B.15 REPL meta-commands

Every REPL meta-command sugar for a Scheme verb:

- `,help <verb>` — pretty print of help(verb)
- `,type <verb>` — contract-of
- `,doc <verb>` — doc-of
- `,arity <verb>` — arity-of
- `,source <verb>` — source-of
- `,examples <verb>` — examples-of
- `,apropos <regex>` — apropos
- `,namespace <ns>` — verbs-in-namespace
- `,time <expr>` — time wrapper
- `,expand <expr>` — macroexpand
- `,trace <verb>` — start tracing
- `,untrace <verb>` — stop tracing
- `,trace-log <verb>` — show log
- `,watch <expr>` — add watch
- `,exit` — leave

## B.16 The five reflexes

Boiled down to five habits:

1. **Ask before guessing.** `(help 'foo)` before you guess what foo does.
2. **Describe before assuming.** `(type-of value)` before you assume the shape.
3. **Expand before debugging.** `(macroexpand form)` before you debug a macro use.
4. **Query before scrolling.** `(cortex/query ...)` or `(apropos ...)` before you scroll.
5. **Introspect before fixing.** `(last-error)` before you edit the code that erred.

## B.17 Common compositions

```
;; enumerate + describe
(map describe (verbs-in-namespace \"cortex\"))

;; filter by shape
(filter (lambda (n) (= 2 (arity-of n))) (map car (snapshot-registry)))

;; introspect a value
(let ((v (some-verb)))
  (list :type (type-of v) :length (and (list? v) (length v))))

;; walk env chain
(define (walk e) (if e (cons (env-vars e) (walk (env-parent e))) '()))
(walk (current-env))

;; trace a session
(,trace my-verb)
(run-session)
(trace-log 'my-verb)
```

Five patterns. Every one is a couple of primitives combined. Compose freely.

## B.18 The cheat-sheet cheat-sheet

If this whole page is too much, remember these ten calls:

```
(help 'foo)
(describe 'foo)
(doc-of 'foo)
(examples-of 'foo)
(source-of 'foo)
(type-of value)
(keys hash)
(apropos \"foo\")
(macroexpand form)
(last-error)
```

Ten calls. You will use them daily. Everything else builds on them.

## B.19 Print

Cut here. Fold in half. Keep near your keyboard.

The cheat-sheet lives on your desk. The habits live in your fingers.

## B.20 Verbatim reference

For final reference, here is the shortest correct Scheme call for each core introspection verb. Copy freely.

```
;; verb metadata
(help 'map)
(describe 'map)
(doc-of 'map)
(contract-of 'map)
(arity-of 'map)
(source-of 'map)
(examples-of 'map)

;; value shape
(type-of value)
(length lst)
(keys hash)
(values hash)
(record-type rec)
(record-fields rec)

;; env
(current-env)
(env-vars (current-env))
(env-parent (current-env))

;; macros
(macroexpand form)
(macroexpand-1 form)

;; reader
(parse \"(+ 1 2)\")

;; errors
(last-error)
(error-message e)
(error-kind e)
(error-location e)
(error-context e)

;; cortex
(cortex/query :subject 's :predicate 'p)
(cortex/record :subject 's :predicate 'p :object 'o :at t :source 'src)

;; registry
(snapshot-registry)

;; search
(apropos \"pattern\")
(verbs-in-namespace \"ns\")

;; llm-augmented
(what-is 'sym)
(explain form)
(fix (last-error))
(pretty-error (last-error))

;; performance
(current-time-ms)
```

That is the whole cheat-sheet.

